Subject: Re: [T2] no arrow on piston

You need to remove the carbon. Use a small chisel with care not to nick the 
aluminum and break the carbon off little chunks at a time. Then polish the 
tops with 220-360 grit. This is the only correct way to verify that arrow.

At 02:38 PM 10/27/2002, you wrote:

>I am installing a used piston (because my other one burned) and the one
>that I got doesn't have an arrow on it because of carbon deposits.
